.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-PROVIDERS 5 "2026-04-20" "shorewall-nft 1.10.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-providers \- multi-ISP provider definitions for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I providers
file defines multiple ISP uplinks (providers) for policy-based routing.
Each provider is assigned a routing table number and an nft connection mark.
Outbound traffic is marked and then routed into the provider's table using
.B ip rule
entries, which the compiler generates separately.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/providers
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
NAME	yes	Provider name (also the ip route table name)
NUMBER	yes	Routing table number (2\(en252)
MARK	yes	Connection mark value for this provider
INTERFACE	yes	Outbound interface for this provider
GATEWAY	no	Gateway IP address (or detect)
OPTIONS	no	Comma-separated options (track, loose, …)
.TE

.SS Options
.TP
.B track
Track connections and ensure replies follow the same provider.
.TP
.B loose
Allow provider to be used even when the interface is down (load-balancing).
.TP
.B fallback
Use as fallback when other providers are down.
.TP
.B balance
Include in load-balancing pool.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Two-ISP configuration with tracking:
.RS
.nf
#NAME   NUMBER  MARK  INTERFACE  GATEWAY     OPTIONS
isp1    1       1     eth0       203.0.113.1  track
isp2    2       2     eth1       198.51.100.1 track,fallback
.fi
.RE
.PP
Load-balanced dual-ISP:
.RS
.nf
isp1    1       1     eth0       203.0.113.1  track,balance
isp2    2       2     eth1       198.51.100.1 track,balance
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-routes (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rtrules (5),
.BR ip\-rule (8)

